			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">After reading through the threads about pet canni/IRE I thought about the means the pure casters have for mana regen. If you take aa's and self buffs only, plus FT15, you get the following picture for standing characters:
<br />

<br />
Enc: MC3 + VoQ + 16 = 37mana/tic
<br />
Mag: MC3 + Water Form 3 + Xegony's + 16 = 29mana/tic
<br />
Nec: MC3 + Force Shield + Seduction of Saryrn + 16 = 71mana/tic
<br />
Wiz: MC3 + Allegiant Familiar + Force Shield + 16 = 29mana/tic (side note: wiz show a much higher passive mana regen than other classes on their magelo profiles, beyond the FT. How does this come??)
<br />

<br />
Of course this leaves out any equipment/horse/meditation, but that would be the same for all classes (except for mage water form on horse). If you now figure in optimal buffs for each class (without bard song), you have these numbers:
<br />

<br />
Enc: Base + Bo9 + SD = 54mana/tic
<br />
Mag: (Base - Xegony) + VoQ + Bo9 + SD = 58mana/tic
<br />
Nec: Base + Bo9 + SD = 88mana/tic
<br />
Wiz: Base + VoQ + Bo9 + SD = 64mana/tic
<br />

<br />
Now, use these numbers to see how long each class would take to med up, assuming a fictive 5000mana pool:
<br />

<br />
Enc: ~ 93tics = ~ 9.3min
<br />
Mag: ~ 86tics = ~ 8.6min
<br />
Nec: ~ 57tics = ~ 5.7min
<br />
Wiz: ~ 78tics = ~ 7.8min
<br />

<br />
Enc, nec and wiz cannot really decrease that med up time. Mages can however take advantage of pet canni...if you use this you see a very different picture. We know top end mages can reach around 300-380mana per pet reclaim. So, if you take our fictive mana pool, it would take 13-17 reclaims to get from OOM to FM. With the right aa's, this would require about 90-120sec, or 15-20tics. Of course, in that time the mage still has his passive mana regeneration, which would get him 870-1160mana during that time. So, effectively you can take away 2-3 uses of pet canni and still be FM. As a result, our mage will be FM after 1.4-1.7min.
<br />

<br />
(For comparison, a mage with IRE would take about 28 reclaims for the same result, using 196sec, or 33tics. In that time he would have passively regenerated about 1900mana, so you could probably take away about 8 uses of canni. He would be FM after about 2.3min.)
<br />

<br />
As you see, a (top end) mage (without IRE) has like three times the mana regeneration of a necro, and almost five times that of an enchanter. You may make from this information whatever you want. To end this post:
<br />

<br />
