				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Izudin wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />

<br />
We know top end mages can reach around 300-380mana per pet reclaim. So, if you take our fictive mana pool, it would take 13-17 reclaims to get from OOM to FM. With the right aa's, this would require about 90-120sec, or 15-20tics. Of course, in that time the mage still has his passive mana regeneration, which would get him 870-1160mana during that time. So, effectively you can take away 2-3 uses of pet canni and still be FM. As a result, our mage will be FM after 1.4-1.7min.
<br />

<br />
(For comparison, a mage with IRE would take about 28 reclaims for the same result, using 196sec, or 33tics. In that time he would have passively regenerated about 1900mana, so you could probably take away about 8 uses of canni. He would be FM after about 2.3min.)
<br />

<br />
As you see, a (top end) mage (without IRE) has like three times the mana regeneration of a necro, and almost five times that of an enchanter. You may make from this information whatever you want. To end this post:
<br />

<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
