				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You're right Sehra, the numbers for the IRE mage are somewhat off, because I assumed the best possible mana saving for summoning efficiency.
<br />

<br />
I did a self test to find out how much time I use to canni up. Test situation: Self buffed + KEI and standing (no horse/elemental form), so my passive mana regen was like 30mana/tic. My mana pool with KEI should be around 4250. I had a pet up and casted destroy summoned on it until I could no longer cast. My mana bar showed 2% then, and I reclaimed the pet I had up and began canni'ing up. It took me 25 reclaims in 3min 45sec to get to 100% mana again.
<br />

<br />
In that time I must have regened about 1100mana passively, so I actually got about 3100mana through reclaims. This would suggest an average of about 125mana per reclaim, which shows that the actual mana saving from summoning efficiency indeed is somewhere in the middle between 1 and 25%.
<br />

<br />
Not really a great result, but still faster than a necro would get his full mana back.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=423546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Izudin</a>, 65 Arch Convoker on Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
