			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">For total downtime nothing else happening mana regen, yeah, it obviously blows everyone else away.  Start creating some hypothetical group situations and comparing it to a necro.  IE: 30 second kill times 15 seconds between mobs, 45 second kill times, so on and so forth.  Sit around in a good xp group for a while and get actual times.  (I timed in pofire for a while and got 50-60 second kill times with 20-30 seconds between mobs)
<br />

<br />
When you do this, you will find that your effective available mana pool over a decent amount of time is still lower than (or very close if you give your test mage a full set of time gear) a necromancer's.  (unless you are giving up fight time for extra canni cycles and dropping your dmg/mob proprotionatley)
<br />

<br />
Everybody has tradeoffs to make.  We do massively less damage than wizards on a (high tier, PoP) boss mob, we do massively more damage than wizards in an xp group.  such is life<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=630419" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Convoke Archly </a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
