				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have logs of myself doing 3 - 4 FBoT and maybe a Burning Sands to finish off each and every mob that the group pulls.  The funny thing is, I only pet canni like once a week.  Maybe when a friend invites me to his guild's NToV raid (I'm usually only caster to do damage to mana draining Aaryonar, high resists heh) and I CoTH 40+ people I pet canni after about 20 CoH.  With VoQ, Xegony's, SD, Emp Robe, and Shield of Auras; I never have problems.  I can deliberately not worry about managing my mana and still not go OOM.  I chained SV on Statue of Rallos Zek and only got to 60% mana before he was dead (~3 min fight) and that was with only KEI and Bo9.  Hell I don't even have a horse.
<br />

<br />
The point...  Mana regen = overrated at high levels.  High level spells are much more efficient than their lower level counterparts (excluding Ancient: Shock of Sun).<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=808887" target="_new"><img border=0 src="http://www.iownjoo.com/freeimghost/hornet/Hornet-Sig2.jpg" /></a>
