				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">With improved reclaim energy can you really go from no mana to full mana from casting and reclaiming pets over and over? Do you get MORE mana back from a pet then you used to cast it with improved reclaim?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Yes.  This is true regardless of which pet you decide to use.  You could (if you wanted to) recast and reclaim your level 24 air pet over and over and continually gain mana... Or your level 4 earth pet.... or your level 34 water pet... or... well you get the idea.
<br />

<br />
Without Improved Reclaim, you will only gain more mana than you used to cast the pet if the pet happens to be the 49 Earth pet, the 50 Monster Summoning 2 pet, or the 65 Earth pet.  On the flip side, canniing these pets exclusively for mana gives more mana back than if you have Improved Reclaim trained.  It's a side effect of their relatively high hit points vs. casting cost.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
