			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Max mana regeneration:
<br />

<br />
W/o horse, bard, FT, MC, or meditate:
<br />

<br />
Ench: Base (4) + VoQ (18) + PotN (8) + SD (9) = 39
<br />
Necro: Base (4) + Lich (50) + PotN (8) + SD (9) + Force Shield (2) = 71
<br />
Magician: Base (4) + VoQ (18) + PotN (8) + SD (9) + Water Form 3 (4) = 43
<br />
Wizard: Base (4) + Allegiant Familiar (8) + VoQ (18) + PotN (8) + SD (9) + Force Shield (2) = 49
<br />

<br />
Enchanters actually lag behind magicians and wizards if you include water form and Familiars.
<br />

<br />
With horse, bard, FT, MC
<br />

<br />
Ench: Base (4 + 21 + 15 + 3) + VoQ (18) + PotN (8) + SD (9) + Bard (21) = 99
<br />
Magician: Base (4 + 21 + 15 + 3) + VoQ (18) + PotN (8) + SD (9) + Bard (21) = 99
<br />
Necro: Base (4 + 21 + 15 + 3) + Lich (50) + PotN (8) + SD (9) + Bard (21) + Force Shield (2) = 133
<br />
Wizard: Base (4 + 21 + 15 + 3) + VoQ (18) + PotN (8) + SD (9) + Bard (21) + Allegiant Familiar (8) + Force Shield (2) = 109
<br />

<br />
If you include mod rods, thats another 7.2 FT (unless the mage is summoning for himself and doesn't have elemental pants). Wizards also get both harvests which equates to an average of about 11.2 FT. Lets not forget Quarm shoulders (or Emperor Robe) for an additional over-meditate.
<br />

<br />
Ench: Base (4 + 21 + 15 + 3) + VoQ (18) + PotN (8) + SD (9) + Bard (21) + Mod Rod (7.2) + Quarm Shoulders (8) = 114.2
<br />
Magician: Base (4 + 21 + 15 + 3) + VoQ (18) + PotN (8) + SD (9) + Bard (21) + Mod Rod (7.2) + Quarm Shoulders (8) = 114.2
<br />
Necro: Base (4 + 21 + 15 + 3) + Lich (50) + PotN (8) + SD (9) + Bard (21) + Force Shield (2) + Mod Rod (7.2) + Quarm Shoulders (8) = 148.2
<br />
Wizard: Base (4 + 21 + 15 + 3) + VoQ (18) + PotN (8) + SD (9) + Bard (21) + Allegiant Familiar (8) + Force Shield (2) + Mod Rod (7.2) + Quarm Shoulders (8) + Harvests (11.2) = 135.4
<br />

<br />
Overall necros with lich have the supreme advantage, followed by wizards. Enchanters and Magicians therefore have the worst med rate.
<br />

<br />
Two things would change these figures though. First is pet canni, which assuming high end gear can often mean 200 FT while pet canni is underway. Then there's also the enchanter AA Gather Mana, which completely refills the enchanter's mana bar. In essence, in a very long fight that just means they have double the mana they started with, and doesn't really help their overall mana regeneration.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://members.cox.net/jmattcrews/wizardbook.jpg" align=left>[65 Arch Convoker] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=204546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Xalmat Lunaire</a> (Human) <<a href="http://www.enshadowed.net/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Enshadowed</a>> ZONE: brellserilis
<br />
[63 High Priest] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=816142" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eiyana Lunaire</a> (Gnome) <<a href="http://www.enshadowed.net/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Evil Empire</a>> ZONE: brellserilis
<br />
<a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewforum.php?f=9" target="_blank" class="postlink">Lead Librarian</a> of <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Magician's Tower</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
