			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">From what I know enchanters keep their gather mana skill for emergencies or after a rez. It also is too limited by its reuse time, so shouldnt be considered for mana regeneration. This leaves mages as the only caster class that can speed up their mana regen...at a rate of 2-3 times that of a necro.
<br />

<br />
Many of you say that they dont think that this ability isnt going to changed, because it was, some weeks ago, officialy confirmed to be "working as intended". But looking at the numbers, I am not too sure about it.
<br />

<br />
If you include the results from the poll I posted on the general forum about mana usage and pet canni, it looks like 1/3 of all mages (that read this board of course) dont have mana problems, even without canni. Another good portion uses to canni to keep their mana up. The rest is limited by mana, be it with or without canni.
<br />

<br />
Now, I did this comparion and the poll with the questions about in my mind, "Is pet canni in the current form too powerful" and "Is pet canni really neccessary?".
<br />

<br />
If you are honest, I think you will have to answer the first question with yes. If we can outregen necros, the masters of mana regen, by such a large margin, then the ability is too good. This could be qualified with the statement "it is too good at the high end, for a non-IRE mage".
<br />

<br />
The responses to the poll show that the second question should also be answered with yes. Pet canni is used by a lot of mages. So the skill should be kept in the game.
<br />

<br />
