<br />

<br />
Is that so?  An IR magician would be first in line for any pet group I would start.  In a situation with limited forms of crowd control, it's good to know I can offtank a nonsummoning mob indefinitely.  I can make a successful group out of almost any makeup.  Two IR magicians in a group is a great backup plan for when things go south in an exp group.  We don't need to hunt down clarity buffs, and we can canni if the situation requires it (asuming we are low on mana in the first place).
<br />

<br />
Actually, it doesn't matter much to me if the magician or magicians I group with have IR or not.  More of us tends to make us more efficient regardless of AA's...  and if any of my non-IR mag buddies runs low on mana, I can help hold off our foes while they canni their mana back....
<br />

<br />
It's good to have choices.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
